node.text:
1 in 2 men & 1 in 3 women in the US will be diagnosed with cancer in their lifetimes. I’m joining Stand Up To Cancer to share the story of one of those cancer patients and spread the message about the importance of cancer research. When we Stand Up together, we have the power to save more lives. It’s #Up2Us to #StandUpToCancer.
 
Watch the inspiring story of Jason Diaz, and learn more about @SU2C’s mission to make a world where every person diagnosed with cancer becomes a long-term survivor during their televised show this Saturday, August 21st at 8pm ET/PT and 7pm CT. StandUpToCancer.org

node.title: Stand Up To Cancer - Jason’s Story

node.text: How to make Steak and Mushrooms Fried Spring Roll! I used leftover NY Strip Steak and cooked Enoki mushrooms seasoned with salt and pepper in avocado oil on high heat. Then I assembled with rice paper, jalapeño, steak, green onions and the Enoki mushrooms. The sauce is 1 tbsp sesame oil, 1 tbsp soy sauce, 1 tsp vinegar, 1/2 tbsp brown sugar, cilantro, sesame seeds and 1 tbsp A1 sauce. #asianfood #leftovers #leftover #steakdinner #easyrecipes #easydinner #dinnerideas #asianrecipes #springrolls #appetizerideas #appetizer #livecooking

node.title: Steak and Mushrooms. See what I do with leftovers!

node.text: Save my recipe for Poached Salmon Soup also known as Vietnamese Canh Chua. The ingredients are 5 cups of water, 3 salmon filets, 1 tsp. Salt, 1 tbsp. Fish sauce, 1/2 tbsp. Sugar, 1/2 onion, 1 cup pineapple, 2 tomatoes, 1/2 packet of Knorr tamarind powder, 1 oz sliced green onions and 1 oz chopped cilantro. Serve over rice or if you’re doing low carb eat it ok it’s own. It’s the perfect healthy dinner and the salmon comes out moist and flakey. @staub_usa #canhchua #vietnamesefood #vietnameserecipes #sinigang #asianfood #asianrecipes #healthyrecipe #easyrecipes #dinnerideas #cookingvideo

node.title: Making Poached Salmon Sour Soup aka Vietnamese Canh Chua

node.text: Save my recipe for for Shrimp Papaya Salad! It’s about 4 cups of shredded green papaya, 3 Thai chilies, 3 cloves of garlic, 1 tbsp. Shrimp paste, 1 tbsp. Sugar, 1 tbsp Fish sauce, juice of 3 limes, 1 cup sliced cherry tomatoes and 1/4 cup chopped cilantro. Top with boiled shrimp and peanuts. @zwilling_usa #shrimppapayasalad #papayasalad #greenpapaya #thairecipes #thaifood #asianrecipes #saladrecipe #lunchideas #recipevideo #livecooking #cookingvideo

node.text:
Save my recipe Vietnamese Pork and Mango Rolls. The pork loin is seasoned with lemongrass, oyster sauce, fish sauce, thick soy sauce and brown sugar. I then assembled my spring rolls with rice paper, pork, red butter lettuce, cucumber, mint and mango. The peanut sauce is peanut butter, hoisin sauce and milk. #springrolls 
#porkloin #vietnameserecipes #vietnamesefood #vietnamesecuisine #vietnamesespringrolls #peanutsauce #easyrecipes #lunchideas #appetizers #recipeoftheday #healthyrecipes

node.text: Save my recipe for Chicken Teriyaki with Asparagus & Rice! It’s a delicious dinner that can be made in under 20 minutes. I seasoned 6 chicken thighs with salt and seared both sides in avocado oil. Then marinade was 1/2 cup yoshida’s sauce, 1/2 cup water, 1 tbsp. minced ginger, 1 tbsp. minced garlic, 1oz sliced green onion and 1/2 tsp. Black pepper. #teriyakichicken #teriyaki #asianrecipes #easydinner #dinnerideas #chickenrecipes #chickenandrice #recipeoftheday #recipeshare #homecooking #livecooking

node.title: Making Chicken Teriyaki with Asparagus for dinner

node.text: Save my recipe for Spicy Peanut Noodles! I used fresh udon noodles that I got from the Asian Market, but you substitute with any noodles you like. The sauce was sesame oil, soy sauce, black vinegar, peanut butter powder, brown sugar, sesame seeds and green onions. Toss in the cooked noodles and add a little water from the pot. Mix everything and then top with chili oil. #spicynoodles #noodles #noodle #asianrecipes #asianfood #simplerecipes #easyrecipes #lunchideas #dinnerideas #recipeshare #peanut #peanutbutter #peanutbutterlover

node.text: Save my recipe for Sesame Crusted Tuna with a Teriyaki Glaze! I made this recipe in Partnership with @samsclub for #aapiheritagemonth. All ingredients sourced at @samsclub #samspartner #ahituna #tunabowl #asianrecipes #healthyrecipes #lunchideas #dinnerideas

node.text: My parents have not seen my brother @le_37 in over a year. He flew in today from SoCal and we pranked my parents. I told them people were coming to inspect the new house, but it was really my brother in a Hazmat Suit. Throughout the years we’ve had many surprises where my brother will just pop up. One time my parents were asleep any my brother came in and placed my 6 month old nephew in their arms. I wish we had footage of all the surprises throughout the years, but this one was the best by far! #prank #pranks #prankster #reunitedanditfeelssogood #familyreunion #reunited #familyovereverything #hiddencamera #family

node.title: My brother surprised my parents in a Hazmat Suit

node.text: For those of you who wish to try this chocolate recipe, I suggest just buying cacao nibs which is sold every where. I started this process because I wanted to learn and also show my girls where chocolate cake from. It’s actually fun once you get past the fermentation process. It tasted like really creamy dark chocolate and melted really fast when you eat it. I wonder because there’s no preservatives or if maybe I added too much oil? Either way, it was delicious and I’ll probably never do it again lol. #cacao #cacaonibs #chocolate #chocolatelab #homemadechocolate #madefromscratch #candymaking #recipevideo #recipes #simplerecipes #dessertrecipe

node.text:
Save my recipe for Air Fryer Crispy Rice! It’s a great way to use leftover rice. I froze the rice for 30 minutes, dusted with flour, cut into cubes and brushed with avocado oil. I then air fried at 425f degree for 15 minutes.
Topped with soft cream cheese and sushi grade salmon. #crispyrice #airfryer #airfryerrecipes #salmonrecipe #phillyroll #sushilovers #easyrecipes #healthyrecipes #quickrecipes #simplerecipes #cookinghack #cookingvideo #leftovers #appetizer

node.text: Save my recipe for Crispy Rice! I’ve done this a few times and I think short grain rice is slightly more glutinous and makes the perfect crispy rice. It stays soft and almost chewy on the inside, but still very crispy on the outside. If you use just regular rice I recommend still giving it flavor with a little rice vinegar, sugar and salt. Check out my previous video on the how to make sushi rice. #crispyrice #friedrice #sushilovers #rice #appetizers #sushi #avocado #leftovers #leftover #easyrecipes #simplerecipes #recipeshare #cookinghack #cookingvideo #lunchideas #cookingathome

node.text: It’s back to school and here’s another lunchbox idea! I made California Rolls with fresh fruit and matcha KitKat bars. For the sushi rice cook 2 cups short grain rice with 2 1/2 cups water. Dissolve 2 tbsp of sugar and 1/2 tbsp salt in 1/3 cup of rice vinegar and pour over rice. Assemble with  Nori, sesame seeds, crab, cucumber and avocado. #backtoschool #lunchboxideas #lunchbox #backtoschoollunch #kidfriendlyfood #kidslunchbox #kidslunch #californiarolls #sushimaking #healthylunch #easyrecipes #healthyrecipe

node.text: I don’t know about you guys, but my kids are not fans of sandwiches and always prefer noodles so I have to be creative when packing for our park outings. Here’s a Asian Inspired Summer Picnic idea with Beef Shoyu Ramen from @samsclub Just microwave for 4 minutes and then separate the noodles from the broth so it doesn’t get mushy. Then I added pork dumplings and matcha KitKat bars for a sweet treat. After playing at the park they gobble everything up with no leftovers.The Beef Shoyu Ramen is also a great back to school lunch idea. #Samspartner #Samsclubsummer #BeefRamen #picnicideas #lunchideas

node.text:
Save my One Pan Turmeric Chicken Recipe for your next dinner. I’m so sorry, I filmed this last year and forgot to share it on Instagram and only shared the long form on my YouTube Channel. Here’s the recipe-
2-3 bone in chicken thighs
¼ tsp. Paprika
¼ tsp. Salt
¼ tsp. Black Pepper
1 tbsp. Avocado oil
⅓ cup diced carrots
⅓ cup diced celery
⅓ cup diced onions
1 tbsp. Minced garlic
2 ¼ cup chicken stock
1 cup rinsed white rice
2 cups cut mushrooms
1 tbsp. Turmeric powder
¼ tsp. Salt
¼ tsp. Black pepper
1 tbsp. Butter
1 tbsp. Lemon juice
INSTRUCTIONS
Season chicken on both sides with paprika, salt and pepper. In a large pan heat avocado oil to medium high heat and place chicken skin side down.
Cook for 2 minutes to sear and flip over.
Add carrots, celery, onions and garlic.
Cook for 1-2 minutes, pour in ¾ cups chicken stock and cover with a lid for 8-10 minutes.
Add rice, remaining chicken stock, turmeric, salt and pepper.
Cover with a lid and cook for another 8-10 minutes or until rice is fully cooked.
Turn off heat and mix in butter and lemon juice. #onepanmeal #tumeric #chickendinner #dinnerrecipes #dinnerideas #quickrecipes #easyrecipes #easydinner #healthyrecipes #healthyrecipe #recipevideo #cookingvideo #recipeshare

node.text: Save my recipe for homemade baked bread! It really takes a whole day to make, but most of it is just waiting for the dough to rise. Start with 1/4 oz yeast, 1 tbsp sugar and two cups warm water. Wait 5 minutes for the yeast to activate and foam. If it doesn’t then that means your yeast is dead. Then add 3 tbsp sugar, 1 tbsp of salt, 2 tbsp vegetable oil and 3 cups of flour. Then knead and slowly add 3 more cups of flour a 1/2 cup at a time. Knead for 10 minutes, place in a warm place like your oven and let rise for 2 hours. Then remove from bowl, section into 2 pieces and knead again and let rise again for m 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 375f for 30 minutes. Knife from @henckels_usa #bakingfromscratch #baking #bakingvideo #bakingbread #bakingrecipes #breadmaking #breadbaking #howtobake #recipevideo #recipes #recipeshare #cookingvideo #homemadebread

node.text: Save my recipe for Homemade Matcha Ice Cream made with the new @ninjakitchen CREAMi. You only need two ingredients which are one can of coconut milk and two scoops matcha green tea mix. The Ninja CREAMi allows you to make multiple homemade frozen treats like ice cream, milkshakes, gelato, sorbet and smoothie bowls! And you can customize any recipe for your dietary needs. It even has a mix in function which came in handy when I added my matcha kitkats.
